Document Title: Corporate Governance & Security Governance Manual – Kahana Inc.

Version: 1.0
Effective Date: March 2026
Owner: CEO
Approved By: Board / Founders

1. Purpose and Scope
This document describes Kahana’s corporate governance structure and how leadership oversees strategy, risk, and internal controls, including information security for the Kahana Oasis platform. It supports SOC 2 Common Criteria related to the control environment (CC1) by showing how management and any board/owners provide oversight and accountability.

It applies to Kahana Inc. as a whole, including all teams involved in delivering and securing Kahana Oasis.

2. Governance Structure and Board / Ownership Oversight
Kahana is led by its founders and executive team, who act as the primary governing body (equivalent to a board for early‑stage companies).

Current executive governance structure:
- CEO (Adam Kershner) provides top-level oversight and final executive accountability.
- CTO oversees engineering and infrastructure governance.
- Security Lead / CISO oversees security governance and compliance operations.
- Functional leads (Engineering, DevOps, Operations, HR, Legal/Privacy) report through executive ownership for policy and control execution.

The governing body:

Sets overall company strategy and risk appetite, including security and privacy priorities.

Reviews major security, product, and financial decisions (e.g., budget, roadmap, key vendor selection).

Reviews significant incidents and their remediation at least annually, or more frequently when needed.

As Kahana grows, the governance structure may formally include independent directors or advisors to strengthen oversight of risk and internal controls.

